LAGOS  – Events of the past year have radically altered long-term risk trends, with new exposures emerging from the pandemic. New ways of working, changes in travel habits, altered supply chain networks and increased reputational risks have impacted established risk trends, with new exposures and increases in claims patterns. It has once again clearly shown the limitations of existing business interruption (BI) coverage for such intangible and systemic risks. HOW NIGERIAN MEN CAN NOW NATURALLY STOP PREMATURE EJACULATION, LOW SPERM COUNT AND OTHER MEN'S SEXUAL NEEDS. MADAM ALWAYS WANTS IT BIGGER, STRONGER AND LONG-LASTING!!! Despite these challenges coupled with the harsh economic realities that have been confronting the global business space including insurance, the Leadway Assurance Company Limited, FBNInsurance Limited, Saham Unitrust and Sovereign Trust Insurance Plc led the pack in prompt claims settlement in the last five years paying a whopping N31.512billion in claims. According to Daily Independent survey, the four insurers stood out in prompt claims settlement with speed through deployment of state-of-the-art technology platforms to drive claims processes. Leadway: Accelerating Insurance Claims Payments Through Technology Saham Unitrust Insurance: Spearheading Claims Settlement Revolution These firms, it was noted, also have in place the best industry head eggs managing various strategic units for optimum results they are currently counting on. According to statistics exclusively obtained by Daily Independent, FBNInsurance Limited between 2018 and 2019 alone had paid out over N14billion in claims, while Sovereign Trust Insurance Plc had paid out a total of N13.3billion in five years, 2016 to 2020. Besides, Saham Unitrust Insurance Limited paid out over N4billion to both individuals and corporate customers within the period of three years, 2018, 2019 and 2020.